What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Packaging Films Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Packaging Films Market

The packaging films market size is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate of 5.25% for the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on packaging films market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecasted period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth.

Packaging films are the type of plastic films composed of different plastic materials such as polypropylene, polyethylene, polyester and polyamide and is used for packaging of products related to medical and pharmaceutical, food, personal care and others. These films have various features such as chemical resistant, lightweight, high transparency, high performance, and easy to open, store, carry and reseal.

The packaging films market is expected to rise in demand due to the high demand for packaging film in various applications such as cosmetics, food and personal care. The rapid urbanization coupled with rise in disposable income is also projected to flourish the growth of the packaging films in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. The high demand for specialty films and high-barrier polymer films which possess water-resistant property as well as rise in the preferences of packaging film made up of bio-plastic materials due to increasing environmental concerns are also anticipated to boost the demand of the packaging films market owing to the above mentioned reasons and is also is projected to grow substantially during the forecast period. Furthermore, the rising environmental concerns driving bio-plastic materials and rapid shift demand towards flexible packaging films are also expected to push the growth of the packaging films market in the above mentioned forecast period.

The major factor which is expected to actively drive the demand of the packaging films market is the rapid innovations in food and beverages packaging and high demand of oriented films. Likewise, the high adoption of sustainable packaging solutions and untapped market in emerging economies as well as the high growth in the cosmetics packaging industry will further offer various growth opportunities for the growth of the packaging films market over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

However, the strict rules and regulations by government pertaining to environmental concern are expected to impede the growth of the packaging films market in the above mentioned forecast period, whereas the various regulations in the industry can challenge the growth of the packaging films market.

